  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Repairing Permanent Homes through Pan American Development Fund</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Affected population(s), Internally displaced persons (IDPs)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The PADF Ayiti Initiative on Reconstruction (REPAIR) project aimed to repair and rehabilitate 4,000 yellow-tagged, earthquake-damaged homes in Port au Prince. The REPAIR project worked through small local contractors from the areas where the yellow houses are located and sought to train and employ 500 builders, masons and small contractors to use improved construction techniques and home repair methodologies.  Houses repaired under the PADF program are tagged and certified as compliant with the Haitian Government&#x2019;s yellow house repair guidelines. In total, 4,018 houses have been repaired.</narrative>
  </description>
